This paper deals with resource allocation in cellular networks with Device-to-Device Communications (D2D), which is a topic related to network infrastructure (NI). The paper also discusses the use of multi-user diversity and local D2D communications, which are concepts related to information theory (IT). The proposed policies aim to improve system performance, which is a topic related to systems and control (SY). The paper also mentions the use of frequency resources, which is a topic related to multimedia (MM). Finally, the paper discusses fairness among users, which is a topic related to cryptography and security (CR).
